  <title xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cultural Programme Mali 2018-2020</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Music and story-telling have very strong positions in Malian society &#x2013; traditionally and continuously.  They function as tools for communal identity creation, mediation and reflection. Therefore, both music and story-telling are some of the best means of communicating positive and hope-giving messages. This project aim to further strengthen the existing Malian national art institutions in music. The program covers a variety of initiatives from capacity building of Conservatoire des Arts et Multimedia (CAMM) and (Institut National des Arts (INA) and continuation of the successful Danish initiated and supported festival SPOT on Mali Music, to new initiatives like e-learning and further musical out-reach from Bamako to other regions in Mali through the institutions&#xB4; existing national networks.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2" xml:lang="EN">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">To use music performance and education to build bridges between different groups with a focus on the young generation.</narrative>
  </description>
